Warner_Robins.Houston County High School (Georgia):
Houston County High School (also referred to as HoCo) is a public high school for grades 9-12 in the city of Warner Robins, Houston, United States. It was founded in 1991 and is part of the Houston County School System.
The school has volleyball, cheerleading, football, basketball, soccer, and tennis teams, the award-winning Black and Silver Brigade marching band, as well as an AFJROTC unit: GA-932.
